<CSS_mediaPointer>
<summary>
The <strong><c>pointer</c></strong> <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS">CSS</see> <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/@media#media_features">media feature</see> tests whether the user has a pointing device (such as a mouse), and if so, how accurate the <strong>primary</strong> pointing device is.
</summary>
<remarks>
<blockquote class="NOTE"><h5>NOTE</h5><para><strong>Note:</strong> If you want to test the accuracy of <strong>any</strong> pointing device, use <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/@media/any-pointer"><c>any-pointer</c></see> instead.</para></blockquote>
<para>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/@media/any-pointer">The <c>any-pointer</c> media feature</see><br/></para>
<para><seealso href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/@media/pointer"> <em>See also on MDN</em> </seealso></para>
</remarks>
